    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-10T15:16:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-10T15:16:00-05:00" n="48"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d48">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 885.73/77</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-10T16:00:00-04:16">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My April 2, 11 a.m., and April 10, 3 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d48fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> In the same conversation referred to in the last telegram
                    the Uruguayan Minister informed me that he had asked for an audience with the
                    President of Argentina before he left for Uruguay this evening, and he has
                    stated to me that he would urge upon him the importance of the granting of the
                    Central &amp; South American Telegraph Co.’s petition for permission to lay
                    cable from Argentina to Montevideo, informing him of the interest the Uruguayan
                    Government had in the matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
